I came here for the first time to play Sunday night trivia. My friend and I got there 30 minutes before trivia started and put our name in before heading to the bar. The hostess said that it would be 30-45 minute wait for a table and that she would text us when it was ready. The bar staff was inattentive and it took them 10-15 minutes before they asked what we wanted to drink.  When it came time for trivia to start, we still hadn’t received a text from the hostess so we went to check on the status of our table. She then informed us that there would be no tables but that we were “welcome to stand around and eaves drop on trivia (yes, eaves drop).”  After about 30 minutes of standing around and playing, we noticed that there were several tables that were clear and unoccupied, so we asked again if we could take a seat. We didn’t receive much of a response, but about 15 minutes after that the hostess sat us.  A waiter never came around until we got back up and asked the hostess if she could find someone to serve us. A waiter then came only to inform us that they were out of the food we ordered. We made different selections but never saw the waiter again until he brought the bill. The food and drinks were good but the service was the worst I’ve experienced.

Came here with a group of 6 for their Sunday Drag Brunch. Make a reservation, it fills up fast. Family friendly atmosphere, great food, bottomless drinks. Wonderful way to spend a Sunday with friends or family. Don't forget to tip the queens! Don't have time to break your $20? The manager will walk around and break them for you! Get there early and get a good view of the center of the room, the performers move around and try to get to everyone in the restaurant, however there are still moments in the show when you can't see or hear them. You'll also notice that your last few refills of mimosa are mostly orange juice, so drink up during the show!

My friends and I went there last weekend to celebrate a birthday. There were 12 in our party. We made reservations through open table and were seated right away. We had very good service. The street corn dip and hush puppies were a big hit. The shrimp and grits were amazing and the crab cakes were also very good. The waiter was great with us and very patient. He had no problem splitting the check into 6. We would definitely go there again in the future.
